            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The swap file name is built from the **complete path** to the file by default, e.g.\n`C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Local\\nvim-data\\swap\\%%?%c%%temp%test.%a.md.swp`\nThe `?` character is reserved (cannot be used in filenames), which causes swapfile creation to fail.\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/444e1ffe3e9c093d764eeda4d469abe46c6c1565/runtime/doc/options.txt#L2329-L2332\n\nThe simplest fix would be to also convert `?` to `%`, though I haven't verified yet if this would cause any regressions.\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/444e1ffe3e9c093d764eeda4d469abe46c6c1565/src/nvim/memline.c#L1450-L1452",
